@startuml seq_slides_follow
title Participant Tracks Host Active Slide

actor "Training Daemon\n(Mac)" as Daemon
participant "Backend\n(FastAPI)" as Backend
participant "WebSocket\nBroadcast" as WS
participant "Participant\nBrowser" as Browser

== Daemon detects slide change (every ~2s poll) ==

Daemon -> Daemon: AppleScript\nget frontmost slide #\n+ presentation name
Daemon -> Daemon: map pptx name → slug/url\nvia slides catalog

alt presentation matched in catalog
  Daemon -> Backend: PUT /api/slides/current\n{slug, url, presentation_name, current_page}
  Backend -> Backend: store state.slides_current
  Backend -> WS: broadcast_state() [all participants]
  Backend -> WS: broadcast {type:"slides_current",\n slides_current: {...}}
  Backend --> Daemon: {ok: true}
else presentation not in catalog (first time only)
  Daemon -> Daemon: beep + log error\n"Presentation inaccessible for participants"
  Daemon -> Backend: DELETE /api/slides/current
  Backend -> WS: broadcast_state() + {type:"slides_current", slides_current: null}
end

== Participant receives slide update ==

WS -> Browser: WS message\n{type:"slides_current", slides_current}

Browser -> Browser: handleMessage()\n→ _onIncomingHostSlidesCurrent(slides_current)

Browser -> Browser: deduplicate by key\n(slug|url|page|name|ts)
note right: skipped if same key as last

Browser -> Browser: _queueHostSlideFollow(slides_current)\n[only if follow is active]

== Follow logic (_applyHostSlideFollow) ==

alt slidesCatalog empty
  Browser -> Backend: GET /api/slides
  Backend --> Browser: {slides: [...]}
  Browser -> Browser: _normalizeSlidesCatalog()
end

Browser -> Browser: _findSlideForHostCurrent()\nmatch by slug / url / name token

alt no matching slide in catalog
  note right Browser: silently skipped
else matching slide found
  Browser -> Browser: _getHostCurrentPage()\nparse current_page → integer

  alt slides overlay not open
    note right Browser: store page, skip navigation
  else PDF.js mode active
    alt different slide or no PDF doc loaded
      Browser -> Browser: _loadSlideIntoViewer(targetSlide)\nload PDF, wait pagesloaded\nthen navigate to stored page
    end

    Browser -> Browser: slidesPdfViewer.currentPageNumber = targetPage\n(clamped to doc page count)
    Browser -> Browser: _setStoredSlidePage(slug, page)
    Browser -> Browser: _renderSlidesMeta()
  else native iframe mode
    Browser -> Browser: reload iframe src\nwith #page=N fragment
  end
end

== Participant initial load (page open / WS reconnect) ==

Browser -> Backend: WS connect
Backend -> Browser: {type:"state", slides_current: {...}, ...}
Browser -> Browser: _onIncomingHostSlidesCurrent(state.slides_current)
note right: same follow path as above

== Participant manually navigates (disables follow) ==

Browser -> Browser: user scrolls or changes page
Browser -> Browser: updateviewarea / pagechanging event
Browser -> Browser: _autoDisableSlidesFollowFromParticipantNav()\n→ Follow button deactivated + blinks

@enduml
